## Recommendation Logic

```typescript
const getRecommendation = (score: number, failures) => {
  if (score >= 80 && !hasA11yFailures(failures)) return 'update_snapshots';
  if (score >= 50 && score < 80) return 'investigate';
  if (score < 50) return 'fix_test';
  if (hasA11yFailures(failures)) return 'investigate';
};
```

---

## Confidence Score Matrix

| Score | Interpretation | Agent Action |
|---|---|---|
| **90-100%** | Very high confidence | Propose auto-update with brief summary |
| **80-89%** | High confidence | Propose update with reasoning |
| **50-79%** | Medium confidence | Show diffs, ask for confirmation |
| **20-49%** | Low confidence | Suggest investigation |
| **0-19%** | Very low confidence | Likely bug, propose test fix |
| **N/A** | A11y failure | Never auto-update, require fix |

